[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 218 (Samoa has not been added as yet).

Data by country, area, or territory for 24 Nov 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesNov24_1606267273.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 43.1% of daily case numbers and 23.0% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours but maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 25.0 million cases. The USA continues to dominate, followed by Brazil, Mexico, Colombia, Canada, and Argentina. Peru, Chile, and Panama also reported more than 1000 cases. And countries/territories reporting more than 500 cases but fewer than 1000 in the past 24 hours include Puerto Rico and Paraguay. Costa Rica did not report any newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

- The European region reported 37.1% of daily case numbers and 55.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 17.2 million. Countries not reporting cases today (24 Nov 2020) include Spain, Sweden, and Kazakhstan, among others. Countries reporting more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours include Russia, Italy, UK, Poland, Germany, and Ukraine. 19 additional countries have reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.8% of daily case numbers and 10.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.86 million cases. Iran is dominant, with continuing record-breaking highs, followed by Jordan, Pakistan, Morocco, Iraq, Palestinian Authority, UAE, and Lebanon. Libya reported more than 500 but less than 1000 cases. Sudan, Djibouti, and Somalia did not report any cases in the past 24 hours.

- The African region reported 1.1% of daily case numbers and 1.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.45 million cases. South Africa maintains its dominance, followed by Algeria, Ethiopia, Uganda, Reunion, and Angola.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 0.86% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.84 million cases. The Philippines, is dominant, followed by Malaysia, Japan, South Korea, French Polynesia, and China. Laos reported 14 newly confirmed cases, almost doubling the number of confirmed cases reported and Mongolia reported 11 new cases.

- The South East Asia region reported 10.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.7% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.4 million cases. As previously, India remains dominant, followed by Indonesia, Bangladesh, Nepal, Myanmar, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives. Bhutan reported 4 new cases.

Impression: Basically unchanged on the regional levels with the continued dominance of Europe and the Americas region representing over 80% of newly confirmed cases and 78% of newly reported deaths in the past 24 hours. With major countries in Europe not reporting over the weekend, European countries are still experiencing significant levels of transmission. The USA maintains its position as the country reporting the most cases on a daily basis, even at a reduced level of reports over the weekend.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 24 Nov 2020, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

