[Countries not reporting cases in the past 24 hours include Pakistan and Madagascar, among others. The number of countries reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours has rebounded from 53 yesterday (23 Nov 2020) to 59 today (24 Nov 2020) but less than 63 on Friday (20 Nov 2020). In the past 24 hours, the USA (177 833 ), India (44 276), Brazil (33 445), and Poland (32 733) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 12 744 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (23-24 Nov 2020). Noteworthy is crossing another million mark -- there have been over 60 million cases reported with over 1.4 million deaths.

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (12 countries) include the USA, India, Brazil, Poland, Russia (24 326), Italy (23 227), Sweden (17 265), Germany (16 258), Iran (13 721), Ukraine (12 287), UK (11 299), and Mexico (10 794). The USA will cross the 13 million case mark in the next 24 hours, and Germany will cross the 1 million case mark later on this week if transmission continues at the same level in both countries.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts are virtually stable having increased by 0.60%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 11.7%. In the USA, representing 30.3% of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, the comparative 7-day averages show a 10.8% increase in confirmed cases and a 37.6% increase in daily reported deaths.

Impression: The comparative 7-day averages show a possible leveling off in daily reported cases but a continued increase in reported deaths. The USA shows continued uncontrolled transmission. - Mod.MPP]
